<! [CDATA[
Bellroy Logo
Bellroy is an Australian accessories brand making carry goods, including bags, folios, wallets, pouches, phone cases, and key covers. It is a certified B Corporation. Bellroy was founded in 2009 by designers Andrew Fallshaw and Hadrien Monloup, and engineers Lina Calabria and Matthew Fallshaw. ‘Bellroy’ is derived from the towns of Bells Beach and Fitzroy, where the company has offices. The brand launched its first wallets in August 2010. As of August 2016, Bellroy had approximately 70 employees.

item.description: Bellroy is an Australian accessories brand making carry goods, including bags, folios, wallets, pouches, phone cases, and key covers. It is a certified B Corporation. Bellroy was founded in 2009 by designers Andrew Fallshaw and Hadrien Monloup, and engineers Lina Calabria and Matthew Fallshaw. ‘Bellroy’ is derived from the towns of Bells Beach and Fitzroy, where the company has offices.
